It is probably domestic activity...as is seen from the apparent assumption of responsibility by Revolutionary Struggle," said Public Order Minister Vyron Polydoras, adding that the attack constituted "an attempt to revive terrorist (activity)" which would fail.
Revolutionary Struggle last struck in May 2005, when it placed an explosive device near the home of former public order minister George Voulgarakis to protest his role in "the Greek state's involvement in the (US) war on terror."
